column1: The Residential Property Price Index (RPPI) was re-launched in
September 2016. The new RPPI covers all market purchases of houses
and apartments by households, both cash and mortgage-funded. The
previously produced index (table HPM01 on the CSO Statbank) covered
only mortgage-based transactions. The new RPPI is superior to the old
one due to the higher volume of transactions in the price model, the
improved quality of the data sources and the addition of better
quality locational information (Eircodes and CSO Census Small Area
Population Statistics).As communicated to users at the launch of the
new RPPI, the original mortgage-based index was to be supported for
an interim period.The CSO wishes to inform users that the maintenance
of the original RPPI on Statbank will cease from August 2019.
